# ISS-562 - scripted test for sge-build packaging tasks.
# Exercises the SGE asset manifest generator and the simple-mode release
# package, against a fresh hello-world project built on the locally-published
# sge-build plugin.

# Generate the asset manifest (on the browser/JS axis, where it is wired) and
# assert its contents via the custom checkManifest task: asset paths present,
# AndroidManifest.xml excluded, text classification + size > 0. This is the
# assertion the CANARY regression must trip.
> checkManifest

# Build the simple-mode release package and assert launchers + jars exist.
> checkReleasePackage

# The generated manifest + release package outputs must physically exist on disk
# (projectMatrix axis target dirs are js-3 / jvm-3).
$ exists game/target/js-3/resource_managed/main/assets.txt
$ exists game/target/jvm-3/release-package/hello-sge/bin/hello-sge
$ exists game/target/jvm-3/release-package/hello-sge/bin/hello-sge.bat
$ exists game/target/jvm-3/release-package/hello-sge/lib
